At this time,
the fire department

5
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:28,375
is still investigating
the cause of the blaze.

6
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:30,791
[TV NEWSCASTER A]
That concludes the news

7
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:33,416
for this hour. Now for the
traffic report, we'll turn to--

8
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,958
This highly anticipated drama

9
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:37,250
will premier tonight
and is expected to--

10
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,958
[TV HOST A] Very special
dog named Pan lives in

11
00:00:40,041 --> 00:00:42,583
America, in the
state of Wisconsin.

12
00:00:42,666 --> 00:00:44,500
He can drag twice his own
body weight and has been...

13
00:00:44,583 --> 00:00:46,916
[ZOROKU] Nothing.
Not a single mention of it.

14
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:05,041
[SANAE]
Hello? Yeah, it's me.

15
00:01:05,125 --> 00:01:07,541
I'm on my way home.

16
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:10,625
[gasps]
Who's Sana?

17
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:08,208
[SANAE hums]

18
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,625
All right, home sweet home.

19
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:36,083
[SANAE gasps]

20
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:44,708
Oh, my gosh, what a cutie!

21
00:03:53,791 --> 00:03:55,541
[ZOROKU]
What are you making there?

22
00:03:56,750 --> 00:04:00,791
[SANAE]
Can't you tell? They're graves.

23
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:05,166
[ZOROKU]
Hmm... Whose graves?

24
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:10,625
[SANAE]
This one's for the bug.

25
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:13,875
This one is for the goldfish.

26
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:17,750
And these two are for
Mommy and Daddy.

27
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:20,416
[SANAE]
Is that... me and Grandpa?

28
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:27,083
[SANA grunts, gasps]

29
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:34,083
Oh, wow.

30
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:35,583
All right, who're you?

31
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:38,125
You're flying! Whoa!

32
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:39,250
[SANA whimpers]

33
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:41,375
You do have some
kind of mystery power!

34
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:44,750
That's so cool!
Wanna come down?

35
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,708
Grandpa told me that
you'd probably be hungry

36
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,791
and I should make you some food.

37
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:50,666
Oh, in case
you were wondering,

38
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:53,625
I'm Zoroku Kashimura's
granddaughter, Sanae.

39
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:55,125
It's nice to meet you!

40
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:57,833
You-- You're his-- Wait, food?

41
00:04:57,916 --> 00:05:01,208
Uh-huh. You are hungry, right?

42
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:03,541
'Cause I can make
you some breakfast!

43
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:06,625
See, I've got a special
mystery power, too.

44
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:09,791
I am known as... the food alien!

45
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,375
Shabam!

46
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:14,083
[SANA whimpers]

47
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:15,541
[SANAE]
Just kidding...

48
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:16,708
You're an alien?

49
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:17,916
What the-- What?

50
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,416
[SANAE]
No! It was just a joke, really!

51
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,458
Sorry!

52
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:26,833
So, grandpa told me
your name is Sana.

53
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:29,458
He told me
some other stuff, too.

54
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:32,166
Like how you used
to live in a scary place,

55
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:34,208
and went through
awful things there.

56
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:37,291
[SANAE] It's okay
if you're scared of me.

57
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:38,916
I understand.

58
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,083
But you're probably
pretty hungry, too.

59
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,500
Just come down
whenever you're ready

60
00:05:42,583 --> 00:05:44,041
and we'll get you some food.

61
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:53,208
[SANAE]
Oink, oink.

62
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:54,541
I'm a nice piggy.

63
00:05:54,625 --> 00:05:57,625
Want to be friends?
No food aliens here.

64
00:05:57,708 --> 00:05:58,666
Oink!

65
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:03,166
[SANAE] Huh? What in the
world just... happened...?

66
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:06,541
[laughing]
That tickles! No!

67
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,125
You're very weird.

68
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:10,916
[SANAE]
Ha-ha! Gotcha!

69
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,166
[SANA squeals]

70
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,666
[SANAE] There, now
we're both buried in pigs!

71
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:15,875
--How do you like that?
--[SANA laughs]

72
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:17,208
[SANAE]
Tickle, tickle, tickle!

73
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,541
--[SANA] Stop it!
--[SANAE] No, I don't think so!

74
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:19,833
You started it!

75
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:26,041
[SANA pants]

76
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:32,208
Anyway, they're cute and all,

77
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:34,791
but where did these
little piggies come from?

78
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:40,500
[music plays]

79
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:43,041
[phone vibrates]

80
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:46,583
[ZOROKU]
Hmm...?

81
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:48,000
What in the world?

82
00:06:48,083 --> 00:06:50,458
[phone vibrates]

83
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:51,666
Yeah, hello?

84
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,666
[SANAE]
Hey, Grandpa!

85
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,166
Did you see my message?

86
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,750
[SANAE]
Pigs! Real, live pigs!

87
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,291
Crazy right?

88
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,708
I guess they're a little smelly,
but they're super cute, too.

89
00:07:01,791 --> 00:07:03,833
Yeah, she's strange,
like you told me.

90
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:05,458
Like really-really!

91
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:08,041
There are pigs everywhere! Pigs!

92
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:09,583
What did she do now?

93
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,375
[SANAE]
It wasn't her fault.

94
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:12,458
I scared her a little,

95
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:14,916
and she reacted
without thinking's all.

96
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,000
[SANA screams]

97
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,625
[ZOROKU]
What was that? Everything okay?

98
00:07:17,708 --> 00:07:19,791
Stop, piggies! Ah!

99
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:22,250
Don't worry. It's fine.

100
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:25,458
Yep. I think she's warming
up to me a little bit, too.

101
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:27,333
She really is adorable.

102
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:31,250
[ZOROKU] Okay. Then just give
me a call if anything comes up.

103
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,625
Bye.

104
00:07:32,708 --> 00:07:34,375
Were you talking to Sanae?

105
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:37,125
--Yeah.
--Is everything okay at home?

106
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:39,500
[ZOROKU]
Yeah. At least, I think so.

107
00:07:39,583 --> 00:07:41,125
We can handle things here.

108
00:07:41,208 --> 00:07:43,291
Why don't you go
home early today?

109
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:44,541
[ZOROKU]
Hmm...

110
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,083
Hey there, it's me.

111
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:51,958
I know it's been a while.

112
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:55,041
Actually, I'm calling because
I have a favor to ask of you.

113
00:07:58,541 --> 00:08:00,541
[SANA]
How'd it go? Was he mad?

114
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,125
No, he's fine.

115
00:08:02,208 --> 00:08:04,458
He was just a
little surprised I think.

116
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,291
Guess I can't blame him.

117
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:07,708
[gasps]

118
00:08:07,791 --> 00:08:10,458
I was surprised when
it started raining pigs, too.

119
00:08:10,541 --> 00:08:13,750
--Sana?
--"Sana-e." But close!

120
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:16,250
It does sound similar
to your name, huh?

121
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:19,750
Sanae...

122
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,166
[SANAE]
Hmm?

123
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:23,583
I'm sorry...

124
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:28,750
Hey, it'll be okay.

125
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:31,291
Don't worry so much.

126
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:32,458
[SANA]
Mm.

127
00:08:32,541 --> 00:08:34,458
So, what would
you like to do now?

128
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:36,166
Do you want a bath?

129
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,208
No.

130
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,250
[SANA] I've got an easier
way of getting clean.

131
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,625
[YONAGA] Wherever Sana is,
I hope she has enough food.

132
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:50,625
[ASAHI] She'll be fine,
don't worry about her.

133
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,291
[phone vibrating]

134
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:54,416
Excuse me.

135
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,708
[KITO]
Harajuku. Omotesando.

136
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:03,916
[SANAE]
There.

137
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,625
How do you like that?
Do they feel tight?

138
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:07,750
[SANA]
Uh, no.

139
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,750
Not too tight, I guess.

140
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:11,500
[SANAE]
Okay, great!

141
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:14,083
Good thing we've still got
some of my old clothes around!

142
00:09:15,583 --> 00:09:18,541
Now, why don't I do your hair?

143
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:21,041
How do you like to wear it?

144
00:09:21,125 --> 00:09:22,791
Well, usually...

145
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,000
...I do it myself.

146
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:30,000
But I just use my
power and it's done.

147
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:33,333
So I don't really
pay attention to it.

148
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:38,250
[SANAE] Oh. Okay. Why don't you
let me take care of it today?

149
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:42,458
[SANAE] There! Well,
give it a good look.

150
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:43,916
[gasps]

151
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:47,791
Pretty cute, isn't it?

152
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:48,958
I like it!

153
00:09:49,041 --> 00:09:51,458
[SANAE giggles]
Okay, next on the list...

154
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:55,208
[gasps]

155
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:56,833
Go ahead, bon appetit!

156
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,583
[SANA] Wha... Wha...
Mmm! What are they?!

157
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:01,416
They're pancakes,
of course, silly.

158
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,958
Haven't you had them before?

159
00:10:03,041 --> 00:10:04,000
Nyo!

160
00:10:06,125 --> 00:10:07,583
Why don't you let me cut them?

161
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:10,750
--[SANA squeals]
--[stomach growls]

162
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,541
Wow, I've never heard
someone's tummy growl

163
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:14,416
while they were eating before!

164
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:19,916
[SANA] So, are you really
Zoroku's granddaughter?

165
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,250
I sure am.

166
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:22,500
[SANA]
You're nothing like him.

167
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:25,166
Oh, you don't think so?

168
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:28,541
Hmm... Let's see, maybe...

169
00:10:28,625 --> 00:10:31,458
"Hey, you. I hate crooked stuff,
you understand?"

170
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:32,625
[SANA]
Nice try.

171
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:35,833
[groans]
Hey, Sanae, are there any left?

172
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:37,625
You finished them already?

173
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,166
--[SANA] Yep.
--I can make some more.

174
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:41,708
[SANA]
Yeah! Yeah!

175
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:44,500
[SANAE]
Okay, wait just a bit.

176
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:46,583
Exactly how long is "a bit"?

177
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,458
--[SANAE] Well, uh...
--'Kay, I waited a bit.

178
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:50,791
--[SANAE] A bit longer.
--Nope!

179
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:51,833
[SANAE gasps]

180
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:56,916
[SANAE] Wow!
That's the biggest pancake

181
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:03,083
I've ever seen in my life!
Are you okay? Ah! Sana?

182
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:05,458
[SANA groans]

183
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:18,791
I was so hungry
I forgot making food

184
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:22,541
that way doesn't work.
It's too inefficient.

185
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:25,250
[SANAE] Hmm... That whole
"law of conservation of energy"

186
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,833
thing, huh?

187
00:11:26,916 --> 00:11:30,000
[SANA groans]
I must eat pancake.

188
00:11:30,083 --> 00:11:32,666
Ah! That's mine! Get off!

189
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,833
Why don't I
just make another batch?

190
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:41,458
[SANA groans]

191
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:45,000
[stair creaks]

192
00:11:46,666 --> 00:11:47,708
[stair creaks]

193
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,166
[SANA gasps]

194
00:11:50,583 --> 00:11:56,666
--[stairs creaking]
--[SANA giggles]

195
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:58,166
[SANA]
Hey, how's it coming?

196
00:11:58,250 --> 00:11:59,500
Are they done yet?

197
00:11:59,583 --> 00:12:01,625
[SANAE]
No. Not yet.

198
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,083
[SANA]
How about now?

199
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:04,458
[SANAE]
Still not done.

200
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:06,125
[SANA]
And now? What about now?

201
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:07,791
Just a little bit longer.

202
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:08,791
[SANA]
Like now?

203
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:10,583
Nope! Like, soon, though.

204
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:16,916
[SANA]
"Meal. Morning"?

205
00:12:18,083 --> 00:12:20,375
[SANAE]
That's right. So, you can read?

206
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,791
[SANA]
Yeah, sure! "Night."

207
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:24,000
[SANAE]
I take care of breakfast,

208
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,625
and Grandpa does dinner.

209
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:28,041
Wait, you mean that he can cook?

210
00:12:28,125 --> 00:12:30,416
Totally. He's really
good at it, too.

211
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,875
[SANA gasps]

212
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,041
[SANA grunts]

213
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:43,750
[SANA]
Help! I can't get this open.

214
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:46,291
[SANAE] Huh? Stop pulling
at it like that.

215
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,916
Slide it sideways.

216
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,041
[SANA]
Oh!

217
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:55,666
[SANA]
Flowers!

218
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,541
[SANAE]
Yeah, Grandpa's growing them.

219
00:12:57,625 --> 00:13:01,500
I help out sometimes, too,
with the watering and stuff.

220
00:13:01,583 --> 00:13:03,250
[SANA]
One isn't blooming.

221
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:06,041
[SANAE] That one doesn't
open up until the sun goes down.

222
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:07,875
It's called the
"queen of night."

223
00:13:07,958 --> 00:13:09,041
[SANA]
Oh...

224
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,125
[SANA sighs]

225
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:23,541
[SANA] It feels strange being
somewhere like this.

226
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:26,208
It's small, and the
lighting is kinda dark.

227
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:28,958
Tidy, but not super clean.

228
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:31,166
It's nothing
like the other place.

229
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,333
[SANA] I guess you really
are Zoroku's granddaughter.

230
00:13:39,416 --> 00:13:41,041
[SANAE]
Huh?

231
00:13:41,125 --> 00:13:42,666
You're a good person, too!

232
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:43,958
[giggles]

233
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:45,916
Why are you so nice to me?

234
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,125
All the other people acted nice,
but they did bad things.

235
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:51,333
Who do you mean?

236
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:54,333
The people
at the research facility.

237
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:55,875
[SANA]
The earliest memories I have

238
00:13:55,958 --> 00:13:59,333
are of the research facility.

239
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:01,541
I may have come
from someplace else,

240
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:03,500
but if so, I don't remember it.

241
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:08,541
[SANA]
One day, I was simply there.

242
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:09,666
[SANA]
The first thing I knew was

243
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,833
the gnawing pain of hunger.

244
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,458
[SANA]
They gave me food, and I ate it.

245
00:14:21,458 --> 00:14:22,791
[SANA] They poked
and prodded at me

246
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:26,083
with metal instruments,
and I let them.

247
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:27,500
[muffled]
Now, face the other way.

248
00:14:29,208 --> 00:14:30,625
[SANA]
I didn't understand language,

249
00:14:30,708 --> 00:14:33,833
but that didn't matter,
because I didn't need it.

250
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,791
I could merge into other
people's consciousness

251
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,541
and become one with them.

252
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,375
[SANA] The line between
myself and others was blurry,

253
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:46,291
a vague boundary that
I couldn't fully grasp.

254
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:47,708
But then one day,

255
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:49,875
two people who looked
identical appeared.

256
00:14:51,916 --> 00:14:54,041
[SANA] At first, I tried
to become one with them,

257
00:14:54,125 --> 00:14:55,583
as I usually did.

258
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,125
[TWINS]
You can't.

259
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:04,750
[TWINS] You are not us.
We are separate beings.

260
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,458
Because I am me.

261
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:07,958
And you are you.

262
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:11,333
[SANA]
Because... I am me...

263
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,041
[SANA] That was when I
learned what language was.

264
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,791
Because for the first time,
I needed it.

265
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,791
And you... are you...

266
00:15:19,875 --> 00:15:21,125
[TWINS]
Yes.

267
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:23,541
There is a boundary
between yourself and others.

268
00:15:23,625 --> 00:15:26,708
Now that you know,
you'll learn to recognize it.

269
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:30,125
I am Yonaga Hinagiri.
I am the younger twin.

270
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:33,625
And I'm Asahi Hinagiri,
the older twin.

271
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,708
[TWINS]
What is your name?

272
00:15:35,791 --> 00:15:37,375
I don't know.

273
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:40,666
[ASAHI] All right, then we'll
just have to give you a name.

274
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,458
[YONAGA] Don't worry,
we'll think of something good.

275
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:44,750
I think I have an idea.

276
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:46,958
Because the
Red Queen loves fish...

277
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,916
...your name will now be Sana.

278
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,416
[SANA]
Sana...

279
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:55,375
[SANA]
That's how I got my name.

280
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:57,625
How I became Sana.

281
00:15:57,708 --> 00:16:00,125
I learned many things
from the twins.

282
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:01,791
They dressed me in cute clothes,

283
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:04,875
and taught me the intricacies
of language and math.

284
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:08,916
They sang songs for me, and
showed me storybooks and poems.

285
00:16:12,166 --> 00:16:13,875
[SANA] I was happy
in the wonderful world

286
00:16:13,958 --> 00:16:15,708
the twins and I shared.

287
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:22,958
[SANA]
But then, I saw it...

288
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:25,166
Huh...?

289
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:28,708
[SANA] It was underground, far
beneath the research facility.

290
00:16:30,083 --> 00:16:32,583
[SANA] What they did
to that person down there.

291
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:35,000
They turned them
into something inhuman.

292
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,458
I was scared. So scared.

293
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:41,833
And then, I ran
from the facility.

294
00:16:41,916 --> 00:16:45,166
Except, the outside
world was scary, too.

295
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:47,208
I didn't know anything...

296
00:16:47,291 --> 00:16:48,333
I was so lost...

297
00:16:48,416 --> 00:16:49,500
[SANAE gasps]

298
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:58,541
[SANA]
Uh...

299
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:01,208
[SANAE]
You're right, Sana.

300
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:04,333
The world can be a truly
scary place sometimes.

301
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,333
We really are alike, you and I.

302
00:17:08,416 --> 00:17:09,833
Our names?

303
00:17:11,458 --> 00:17:14,750
[SANAE]
It's okay. It'll be okay.

304
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:17,791
[ICHIJO]
Be more careful, Naito.

305
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:18,916
You're making a mess.

306
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,791
[NAITO]
So what if I am?

307
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:22,500
I'm starving here.

308
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:25,125
[ICHIJO] Well, at least try
not to get it on the seats.

309
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:26,916
I'm the one who'll hear
about it from the director

310
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,291
if they get stained.

311
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:30,708
[NAITO] Man, are you always
this uptight, Ichijo?

312
00:17:30,791 --> 00:17:33,166
How old are you, anyway, 80?

313
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,375
[ICHIJO]
I'm 26.

314
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:37,125
Oh, really? That young, huh?

315
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:39,000
You had better
not be hitting on me.

316
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:40,416
[NAITO]
Of course not!

317
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,166
My point was, you're probably
too young to know

318
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,083
anything about <i>takenoko</i> - <i>zoku</i> .

319
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:46,458
The dance groups that
were popular a few decades ago?

320
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:51,041
Yeah. Buncha kids
dancing on the sidewalk.

321
00:17:51,125 --> 00:17:55,583
Well, back then, I was still the
low man on the totem pole.

322
00:17:55,666 --> 00:17:57,375
On weekends,
I got stuck working security

323
00:17:57,458 --> 00:17:59,416
in pedestrian-only zones.

324
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:01,208
And one day, I saw
this grown man arguing with

325
00:18:01,291 --> 00:18:03,166
a group of dancers, shouting
something about how

326
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:04,958
he "hated crooked stuff."

327
00:18:05,041 --> 00:18:07,125
I thought to myself,
"This guy might be crazy,

328
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:09,583
but he's a lot less annoying
than those kids are."

329
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:10,958
Yeah?

330
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:12,625
[NAITO] Somehow or another
we got to talking.

331
00:18:12,708 --> 00:18:15,625
That was 30 years ago, and
we've been buddies ever since.

332
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:18,375
Though I haven't seen him
in the last five years.

333
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:19,708
Well, this is a first.

334
00:18:19,791 --> 00:18:21,291
I've never heard you talk
about a friend before.

335
00:18:21,375 --> 00:18:22,750
'Least I don't think so.

336
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,750
It sounds like the two of
you must be pretty close.

337
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:26,708
Nah, not at all.

338
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:28,875
He's an uptight, stubborn
old stick in the mud.

339
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:31,083
We couldn't be more
different if we tried!

340
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,208
Hey, look at this.

341
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:34,000
It's the homepage
for his company.

342
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:36,750
He's a "flower coordinator."
Fancy, huh?

343
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,708
[ICHIJO] Sounds to me
like you really are close.

344
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:44,000
[SANA sighs]
That was great, thank you!

345
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,750
Hey, I know.
Let's go to the facility!

346
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,333
What?

347
00:18:50,416 --> 00:18:52,958
I've got plenty of energy now
after eating all those pancakes.

348
00:18:53,041 --> 00:18:54,958
Let's go and destroy it!

349
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,666
[SANAE]
Mm... Well...

350
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,791
I can do it! I can. Totally!

351
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:02,125
Believe it! Just pack up
some food and come with me.

352
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:04,791
Oh, yeah. Where
is Zoroku, anyway?

353
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:07,208
I think he's
at his shop, working.

354
00:19:07,291 --> 00:19:10,125
Oh, right. His shop.
I knew that!

355
00:19:10,208 --> 00:19:12,541
[SANAE] Wow. Some sleep
and a million pancakes,

356
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,708
and she's bouncing
off the walls.

357
00:19:14,791 --> 00:19:16,041
[SANA]
Huh? What's up?

358
00:19:16,125 --> 00:19:17,250
Nothing.

359
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,375
Sana. Do you think
you can wait for a bit?

360
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:20,416
I just need to clean up.

361
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,333
Nope. Let's go get him.

362
00:19:22,416 --> 00:19:23,458
[SANAE gasps]

363
00:19:25,458 --> 00:19:26,833
[BOTH scream]

364
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:28,416
[SANA] What's the heck?!
I didn't do this on purpose,

365
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,250
I swear! Just give me a second
and I'll figure something out!

366
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:32,875
Really! Any second now!

367
00:19:32,958 --> 00:19:34,750
[BOTH scream]

368
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,500
[BOTH screaming]

369
00:19:43,583 --> 00:19:45,500
--[SANAE] Someone help!
--[SANA] What now?

370
00:19:51,458 --> 00:19:54,875
Aw, penguins! So adorable!

371
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,000
[SANA]
Huh?

372
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:58,000
You mean you've
never seen a penguin?

373
00:19:58,083 --> 00:20:01,083
Oh, wow! It's freezing.

374
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:05,291
Is this the South Pole?
I've never been here before.

375
00:20:05,375 --> 00:20:08,750
[giggles]
I haven't been here either.

376
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,583
What'd I tell you? We are alike.

377
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:15,250
[SANA]
Boop! This one's small.

378
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:16,833
It's just a baby.

379
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:18,625
Super cute, huh?

380
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:20,708
Uh-huh, adorable.

381
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:22,916
So, uh, you cold, too?

382
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:31,791
[CHINATSU] Boss, which
cylinder did you want to use?

383
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:37,958
[SANAE]
You're amazing, Sana.

384
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:40,166
Can you go anywhere?

385
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:41,750
Um... Well, yeah.

386
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:44,083
I can. So where to next?

387
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:46,708
[SANAE]
Hmm. How about home?

388
00:20:46,791 --> 00:20:47,791
Ah...

389
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:49,916
We shouldn't stay
gone for too long.

390
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,583
And Grandpa's going to
wonder where we went.

391
00:20:52,666 --> 00:20:54,750
Do you think
that he'll be angry?

392
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:59,000
Well, no. But he
might be kinda worried.

393
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:00,416
Really?

394
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,916
Yes, really.

395
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,750
So then, home now?

396
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:06,791
[SANA]
Sure.

397
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:09,583
[BOTH yelp]

398
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:12,708
[SANA whines]
I smell like pig!

399
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:14,083
[BOTH yelp]

400
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:16,541
[ICHIRO]
Hmm?

401
00:21:17,583 --> 00:21:18,750
[ICHIRO yells]

402
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:21,375
[CHINATSU]
Ah! Where'd the pigs come from?

403
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,208
[CHINATSU screams]

404
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:24,666
[ICHIRO]
What are they doing here?!

405
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,583
[CHINATSU] Revenge for the
pork chops I had yesterday?!

406
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:27,916
[BOTH]
Uh-oh...

407
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,000
--[CHINATSU whines, screams]
--[glass shattering]

408
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:31,208
--[ICHIRO yelps]
--[glass shattering]

409
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:36,000
[NAITO]
Hey, Roku,

410
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:37,583
--How's it going?
--[SANA wails]

411
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:40,500
Explain yourself, now!

412
00:21:40,583 --> 00:21:42,458
Grandpa, we're sorry. Really!

413
00:21:42,541 --> 00:21:44,208
[SANA wails]

414
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:45,416
[SANAE] We didn't mean
for any of this...

415
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:48,166
I want an explanation,
not excuses!

416
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,625
Right, time to go.

417
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:51,625
We've got work
to do here, Naito.

418
00:21:51,708 --> 00:21:52,916
Keep cool.

419
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,750
[SUBORDINATE A]
This is really sudden.

420
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:30,458
I don't know if I can do it.

421
00:23:31,541 --> 00:23:33,375
Yes. Right.

422
00:23:33,458 --> 00:23:35,208
I'll make the arrangements now.

423
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:45,583
I think it's about
time we called Minnie C.

424
00:23:47,416 --> 00:23:48,666
[SANA]
"Cards."

